+{"id":"frankenpandas-xp63","title":"fd90.77: DISC-012 - datetime tz format string differs from pandas (ISO 8601 vs space+offset)","description":"Continuation of fd90.76 conformance failure analysis. The 3rd packet failure (FP-P2D-429 csv_read_frame_parse_dates_mixed_timezone_strict) has a different root cause from DISC-011: it is a datetime-with-tz string format divergence. Our parse_dates output formats tz-aware timestamps as ISO 8601 (2024-01-15T10:30:00Z); pandas formats with a space separator and explicit offset (2024-01-15 10:30:00+00:00). Document as DISC-012 ACCEPTED (string format, semantics identical). The fix is mechanical (change format string in fp-frame's datetime serializer) but would touch a hot path so deserves its own bead. Just file the DISC entry now to capture the discrepancy for users running into it.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"docs","assignee":"cc-pandas-2","created_at":"2026-04-26T07:33:21.074686175Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-26T07:35:01.103882527Z","closed_at":"2026-04-26T07:35:01.101323312Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["discrepancy","docs","fd90","review"]}
