 {"id":"frankenpandas-y1p","title":"Add DataFrame numeric transform packet conformance coverage","description":"Testing-conformance fallback audit found README-advertised DataFrame numeric transform APIs implemented in fp-frame but not exposed through packet conformance: DataFrame.abs, clip, round, and astype. Add FixtureOperation variants, pandas oracle dispatch, strict/hardened packet fixtures, and a packet filter test so these APIs are frozen against the pandas oracle. Evidence: README advertises DataFrame transform/dtype parity; fp-frame implements DataFrame::abs, DataFrame::clip, DataFrame::round, DataFrame::astype; fp-conformance has SeriesAstype/SeriesClip/SeriesAbs/SeriesRound but no DataFrame equivalents.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-04-18T01:33:47.057904091Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-18T01:47:00.489424648Z","closed_at":"2026-04-18T01:47:00.487179800Z","close_reason":"Added DataFrame numeric transform packet conformance coverage with fmt/check/clippy/focused packet test passing","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["conformance","dataframe","transform"]}
